ext_descriptions.ext_description:
	A circular_runout_tolerance is a type of
	.
	The set of referenced datums shall contain an axis.
	There are four kinds of circular_runout_tolerances:


radial;

axial;

in any direction;

in a specified direction.



		Refer to the definition of circular run-out tolerance in ISO 1101:1999 for a complete description
		of the different tolerance zones.
